Good morning Chanel, 

I was able to get the claim approved today. The GAP payout will be $6086.19. I understand that this leaves a shortfall, and I wanted to explain why this is. Please see the below definition for Total Qualifying Amount:

Total Qualifying Amount means:
- For a Used Vehicle: One Hundred and sixty percent (160%) of the Canadian Black Book value for the Vehicle at the time of sale or Purchase Price, whichever is the lesser. Total Qualifying Amount is the amount used to determine the GAP Cover cost and for the calculation purposes in the event Your request a payment under this GAP Cover. 

The purchase price of the vehicle as per the Bill of Sale is $20,122.00 and the CBB value of the vehicle is $24625.00. 160% of $20,122.00 is $32195.20. This is the maximum amount of coverage purchased under the Contract. The amount financed is greater than this amount, so when we do a calculation of the Outstanding Loan Amount we have to look at the amount as if you had only financed the Total Qualifying Amount. This is the reason that the amount provided as the GAP payout does not cover the full amount of the actual outstanding loan. 

In order for us to send out the cheque to TD Auto Finance we require our proof of loss form to be signed and returned to us. I have attached it to this email. Once I have this back, I can provide you with the tracking number as it becomes available.

Please let me know if you have any questions.

Sarah Gabor
